-------Lecture 2--------------


Transition from SOA to Cloud:


SOA is a method of software design that produces set of services that are loosely coupled and accessible from different applications in separate business domains



Like SOA, Cloud computing is also service-oriented


It is like Hyperlevel SOA..It operates same way as SOA


Major difference is cloud computing require service level agreements




SLA:

-They are like contract between end users and cloud service providers




Cloud computing Key Enabling Technologies:

-Cloud Datacenters

-Virtualization

-Cloud APIs

-Cloud Storage

-Cloud Database  : Cloud computing is not suited well with Relational Databases.
They are suited well with non-relational databases.


Bcoz scalability relability not there with this. But with non-relational scalability is there



Virtualization: Multiple OS run on same system



